description: The Jiansong Art Museum of Korea is the leading ancient calligraphy and painting collection museum in Korea. It was established in 1938 and is located in Seongbuk 2-dong, Seongbuk-gu, Seoul. The Baohua Pavilion, the main building of the art museum, houses the cultural relics collected by Mr. Quan Yingbi throughout his life, most of which are national treasures.

place_name: Museum of Art, Seoul National University
description: The Seoul National University Museum of Art has been striving to present new, original and contemporary art to the world. The Seoul National University Museum of Art, which has been open since the 2006 "Modern Art Road Invitation" exhibition, has provided exhibitions, events, and educational programs that are sensitive to changes in the times such as contemporary art trends, social focus, and the role of art museums.
